(
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFF58FE5F2B3EFDE5" box="[159,258,497,524]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Figs 1–6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C2998FFD3801BFF50FD97296DFA82" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF50FD972E2DFD75" blockId="2.[151,1437,569,1748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFF50FD972B2EFDBA" bold="true" box="[151,274,569,595]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD3801BFE55FD942812FDBA" authorityName="Silva-Neto, Garcia Aldrete &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2019" box="[402,558,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uariniensis">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFE55FD942812FDBA" box="[402,558,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">E. uariniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from it by the shape of the anterior margin of the mesal endophallic sclerite, by the posterior median processes of the central sclerite of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFB92FDF32EA6FD91" box="[1109,1178,605,632]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), which are more widened distally and by presenting the anterior endophallic sclerites larger (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC79FD2F2E3FFD75" box="[958,1027,641,668]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF00FD0B2ED1FC9A" blockId="2.[151,1437,569,1748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFF00FD0B2B37FD56" bold="true" box="[199,267,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Color</emphasis>
(in 80% ethanol). Head brown, with pattern of dark spots like a mask in vertex and frontal area; dark brown compounds eyes; ocelli hyaline, with ochre centripetal crescents; anteclypeus, clypeus and labrum brown, postclypeus with converging diagonal ochre bands; genae dark brown to ochre. Maxillary palps pale brown. Legs: Coxae with brown spot; trochanters, femora and tarsi 1 light brown, tarsi 2–3 brown. Forewings as in group diagnosis (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFF27FC9B2B1DFCA6" box="[224,289,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), veins brown, with brown spots on vein ends; pterostigma pale brown, proximally paler. Hindwing as in group diagnosis (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFEB2FCF72B86FC9A" box="[373,442,857,883]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), veins brown. Hypandrium brown. Epiproct and paraprocts light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF00FCD3296DFA82" blockId="2.[151,1437,569,1748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFF00FCD32B67FC7E" bold="true" box="[199,347,893,919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Morphology</emphasis>
. As in diagnosis, plus the following: Head (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC91FCD329A1FC7E" box="[854,925,893,919]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): H/MxW: 1.55; compound eyes large, H/D: 2.48; IO/MxW: 0.72. Outer cusp of lacinial tips broad, with seven denticles; Mx4/Mx2: 1.26. Forewings (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFA8FFC0F2FB7FC52" box="[1352,1419,929,955]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
): L/W: 2.55. Pterostigma: lp/wp: 5.71, areola postica high and wide, apex rounded: al/ah: 1.70. Hindwings (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFA8FFC6B2FB2FC36" box="[1352,1422,965,991]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
): l/w: 2.87. Central sclerite of the hypandrium as in diagnosis of the group (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC2BFC472E0EFBED" box="[1004,1074,1001,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), anterior margin convex; basal section slightly wider than long, postero-lateral angle with short rounded processes, with several macrosetae. Phallosome (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFF3FFB9F2B02FBA5" box="[248,318,1073,1100]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): side struts U-shaped; external parameres narrow, with pores; anterior pair of endophallic sclerites transverse, with ends converging mesally, posterior margin with several pointed teeth; lateral pair laminar, apically somewhat truncate, with short process as illustrated; mesal sclerite inverted U shaped, central anterior area less sclerotized, usually with medially concave anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFCFEFB3329D9FB51" box="[825,997,1181,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,607,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[151,1435,597,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Variations in the shape of the mesal endophallic sclerite of Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. 12 and 13. Pará (Brazil). 14 and 15. Valle del Cauca (Colombia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488312/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Figs 12, 14, 15</figureCitation>
), postero-mesal sclerites elongate, narrow, distally acuminate, each connected to the external parameres (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC44FB6F29FBFB35" box="[899,967,1217,1244]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Variations in the shape of this endophallic sclerite are presented in 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFE12FB4B2847FAE9" box="[469,635,1253,1280]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,607,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[151,1435,597,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Variations in the shape of the mesal endophallic sclerite of Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. 12 and 13. Pará (Brazil). 14 and 15. Valle del Cauca (Colombia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488312/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Figures 12–15</figureCitation>
. Paraprocts ovoid (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC9FFB4B29A2FB16" box="[856,926,1253,1279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), with a dense field of setae and macrosetae distally, an apically spatulate macrosetae near the inner margin; sensory fields with 34–36 trichobothrias on basal rosettes. Epiproct (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFEACFA832B93FAAE" box="[363,431,1325,1351]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) semioval, with two lateral macrosetae, basal field with three setae and microsetae, other setae and microsetae scattered in the distal field, as illustrated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
